{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-15T15:31:06.699Z","tool_name":"update_topic","tool_id":"update_topic__update_topic_1781537466695_0","parameters":{"title":"Failure Analysis & Stabilized SSA Attempt","strategic_intent":"Analyze why SSA failed and try a more stable implementation.","summary":"The initial SSA experiments failed to train, with accuracy remaining near random chance. Analysis suggests that categorical sampling across all intermediate layers causes signal attenuation and training instability due to the competitive nature of the softmax function. I am now attempting to stabilize SSA by using it only in the final feature layer and investigating if a higher temperature or residual connection can enable convergence. This will help determine if the 'Softmax Sampling' idea is viable even in a limited capacity."}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-15T15:31:07.020Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file__write_file_1781537467017_1","parameters":{"file_path":"src/model_mixed.py","content":"import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom .ssa import SoftmaxSamplingActivation\n\ncfg = {\n    'VGG11': [64, 'M', 128, 'M', 256, 256, 'M', 512, 512, 'M', 512, 512, 'M'],\n}\n\nclass VGG_Mixed(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, vgg_name, nclass, tau=1.0, hard=False):\n        super(VGG_Mixed, self).__init__()\n        self.features = self._make_layers(cfg[vgg_name], tau, hard)\n        self.classifier = nn.Linear(512, nclass)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        out = self.features(x)\n        out = out.view(out.size(0), -1)\n        out = self.classifier(out)\n        return out\n\n    def _make_layers(self, cfg, tau, hard):\n        layers = []\n        in_channels = 3\n        # Only use SSA for the LAST feature layer\n        num_layers = len([x for x in cfg if x != 'M'])\n        layer_idx = 0\n        for x in cfg:\n            if x == 'M':\n                layers += [nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2)]\n            else:\n                layer_idx += 1\n                if layer_idx == num_layers:\n                    activation = SoftmaxSamplingActivation(tau=tau, hard=hard)\n                    print(f\"Using SSA for layer {layer_idx}\")\n                else:\n                    activation = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)\n                \n                layers += [nn.Conv2d(in_channels, x, kernel_size=3, padding=1),\n                           nn.BatchNorm2d(x),\n                           activation]\n                in_channels = x\n        return nn.Sequential(*layers)\n"}}
{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-06-15T15:31:07.039Z","tool_id":"update_topic__update_topic_1781537466695_0","status":"success","output":"## 📂 Topic: **Failure Analysis & Stabilized SSA Attempt**\n\n**Summary:**\nThe initial SSA experiments failed to train, with accuracy remaining near random chance. Analysis suggests that categorical sampling across all intermediate layers causes signal attenuation and training instability due to the competitive nature of the softmax function. I am now attempting to stabilize SSA by using it only in the final feature layer and investigating if a higher temperature or residual connection can enable convergence. This will help determine if the 'Softmax Sampling' idea is viable even in a limited capacity.\n\n> [!STRATEGY]\n> **Intent:** Analyze why SSA failed and try a more stable implementation."}
