{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-15T15:47:03.564Z","tool_name":"update_topic","tool_id":"update_topic__update_topic_1781538423560_0","parameters":{"title":"Research Completion & Final Reporting","summary":"I have completed the research on 'Sampling Neural Networks'. Through a series of experiments on CIFAR-10, I investigated the 'Softmax Sampling Activation' (SSA) concept. My analysis revealed that while categorical sampling is a powerful concept, it faces significant training challenges including signal attenuation and high gradient variance in deep architectures. I successfully demonstrated convergence by applying SSA selectively in the final feature layer using Gumbel-Softmax reparameterization. All findings, including the comparison with ReLU and the failure modes of pure SSA networks, are now documented in the final REPORT.md and README.md.","strategic_intent":"Finalize research findings and document results."}}
